  "body": "In MPT, there are 3 kinds of nodes, Leaf Node, Branch Node and Extension Node and the branch node has 16 children\r\n\r\n\r\nWith massive amounts of data being stored and keys being hashed, the root layer should be the branch node\r\n\r\n\r\nso can we make The MPT tree  splited into 16 sub MPT  shards  and each shard in parallel?  \r\n\r\nThe advantage of doing this is that  we can parallelize the related operations of mpt include insert/delete/hash calculation . In this way, we can greatly improve the performance of commit and hash calculations",
